  "prompt": "What world nations think about the surgical strike on POK launch pads and what is the reaction of Pakistan?",
  "response": "The surgical strikes carried out by the Indian Army on terror launch pads in Pakistan-occupied Kashmir (PoK) in 2016 garnered varied reactions from different nations and from Pakistan itself. Here's an overview:\n\n### International Reactions:\n\n1. **United States:**\n   - The U.S. urged both India and Pakistan to exercise restraint and encouraged dialogue to resolve their differences. They acknowledged India's right to self-defense but emphasized the importance of de-escalation.\n\n2. **China:**\n   - China expressed concern over the escalation of tensions and called for restraint from both sides. They emphasized that the issue should be resolved through dialogue and consultation.\n\n3. **Russia:**\n   - Russia supported India's right to self-defense and described the surgical strikes as a \"measured response\" to terrorism. They called for a peaceful resolution of the conflict.\n\n4. **United Kingdom:**\n   - The UK condemned terrorism and supported India's right to self-defense. They urged both nations to engage in dialogue to resolve the underlying issues.\n\n5. **France:**\n   - France stood in solidarity with India in the fight against terrorism and acknowledged India's right to defend itself.\n\n6. **Germany:**\n   - Germany condemned terrorism and called for de-escalation and diplomatic efforts to resolve the conflict.\n\n7. **Japan:**\n   - Japan expressed concern over the situation and urged both countries to exercise restraint and seek a peaceful solution.\n\n### Pakistan's Reaction:\n\nPakistan vehemently denied the surgical strikes, asserting that no such military action occurred and that the Indian claims were false. They accused India of attempting to divert attention from internal issues and escalating tensions. Pakistan's Foreign Office condemned the alleged strikes and stated that they would respond to any aggression at a time and place of their choosing.\n\nAdditionally, Pakistan took several diplomatic steps:\n\n- **Ceasefire Violations:** Pakistan reported increased ceasefire violations along the Line of Control (LoC) following the strikes.\n- **Diplomatic Protests:** Pakistan lodged strong protests with the international community, including the United Nations, against what they described as Indian aggression.\n- **Internal Measures:** Pakistan claimed to have taken internal security measures to safeguard against future attacks and to counter terrorism.\n\nOverall, while many nations expressed support for India's right to self-defense and condemned terrorism, they also emphasized the importance of de-escalation and dialogue. Pakistan, on the other hand, outright rejected the occurrence of the surgical strikes and maintained a stance of strong opposition to India's actions.",
